  "body": "<!-- If you need help or think you have found a bug, please help us with your issue by entering the following information (otherwise you can delete this text): -->\r\n\r\nOutput of `helm version`:\r\nNot applicable.\r\n\r\nOutput of `kubectl version`:\r\nNot applicable.\r\n\r\nCloud Provider/Platform (AKS, GKE, Minikube etc.): \r\nNot applicable.\r\n\r\nCurrently `helm lint` does not fail when there is an error in dependent chart. `helm lint --strict` fails which is surprising for as the helm of the --strict flag is `fail on lint warnings` - which means that helm lint should detect warnings and --strict just to transform the warnings to errors.\r\n\r\nIt will be useful if `helm lint` is able to lint also dependent charts (in `charts/`).\r\n\r\n",
